# Train set & Test set
train <- (Year<2005)
Smarket.2005 <- Smarket[!train,] # Test set
dim(Smarket.2005)
## [1] 252   9
Direction.2005 <- Direction[!train]
glm.fits <- glm(Direction~Lag1+Lag2+Lag3+Lag4+Lag5+Volume,data=Smarket,family=binomial,subset=train)
glm.probs <- predict(glm.fits,Smarket.2005,type="response")
glm.pred <- rep("Down",252)
glm.pred[glm.probs>.5] <- "Up"
table(glm.pred,Direction.2005)
##         Direction.2005
## glm.pred Down Up
##     Down   77 97
##     Up     34 44
mean(glm.pred==Direction.2005) # Accuracy
## [1] 0.4801587
mean(glm.pred!=Direction.2005) # Misclassification error
## [1] 0.5198413
glm.fits <- glm(Direction~Lag1+Lag2,data=Smarket,family=binomial,subset=train)
glm.probs <- predict(glm.fits,Smarket.2005,type="response")
glm.pred <- rep("Down",252)

Linear Discriminant Analysis

library(MASS)
lda.fit <- lda(Direction~Lag1+Lag2,data=Smarket,subset=train)
lda.fit

## lda(Direction ~ Lag1 + Lag2, data = Smarket, subset = train)

Models using Logistic Regression, LDA, QDA

Build models for predicting stock market data

glm.fit <- glm(Direction~Lag1+Lag2,data=Smarket,family=binomial,subset=train)
lda.fit <- lda(Direction~Lag1+Lag2,data=Smarket,subset=train) 
qda.fit <- qda(Direction~Lag1+Lag2,data=Smarket,subset=train)

Confusion Matrix Revisited

Predicting Values

glm.pred <- predict(glm.fit, Smarket.2005, type = "response")
lda.pred <- predict(lda.fit, Smarket.2005)
qda.pred <- predict(qda.fit, Smarket.2005)

ROC curves

library(pROC)
## Type 'citation("pROC")' for a citation.
## 
## Attaching package: 'pROC'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     cov, smooth, var
glm.roc<-roc(Direction.2005,glm.pred)
## Setting levels: control = Down, case = Up
## Setting direction: controls < cases
lda.roc<-roc(Direction.2005,lda.pred$posterior[,2])
## Setting levels: control = Down, case = Up
## Setting direction: controls < cases
qda.roc<-roc(Direction.2005,qda.pred$posterior[,2])
## Setting levels: control = Down, case = Up
## Setting direction: controls < cases
plot(glm.roc,col=1,main="GLM")

plot(lda.roc,col = "red",main="LDA")

plot(qda.roc,col = "darkgreen",main="QDA")

ROC curves and AUC

names(glm.roc)
##  [1] "percent"            "sensitivities"      "specificities"     
##  [4] "thresholds"         "direction"          "cases"             
##  [7] "controls"           "fun.sesp"           "auc"               
## [10] "call"               "original.predictor" "original.response" 
## [13] "predictor"          "response"           "levels"
glm.roc <-glm.roc[c("specificities","sensitivities","thresholds","auc")]
lda.roc <-lda.roc[c("specificities","sensitivities","thresholds","auc")]
qda.roc <-qda.roc[c("specificities","sensitivities","thresholds","auc")]

plot(x=(1-glm.roc$specificities),y=glm.roc$sensitivities,xlim=c(0,1),ylim=c(0,1),type="l",xlab="1-Specificity",ylab = "Sensitivity",main = "ROC curve of LR")

plot(y=lda.roc$sensitivities,x=(1-lda.roc$specificities),col = "red",type="l", main="ROC curve of LDA")

plot(y=qda.roc$sensitivities,x=(1-qda.roc$specificities),col = "darkgreen",type="l", main="ROC curve of QDA")

glm.roc$auc

lda.roc$auc
